Albion Farm Shop & CafeClick to open side panel for more information is a family-run business in the Saddleworth hills, renowned for its panoramic views and commitment to high-quality, locally-reared produce. It is a "one-stop shop" for those who appreciate traditional British farm food and a cozy cafe atmosphere.

Farm Shop Specialties: Offers home-reared pedigree Welsh Black beef, home-cured bacon, and a wide selection of artisanal cheeses, preserves, and Great British hampers.

Cafe Highlights: Known for its "Great British Breakfast" and traditional northern dishes like rag pudding and cheese and onion pie.

Scenic Setting: Features a terrace and large windows with stunning views across the Delph and Greenfield valleys.

Family Atmosphere: Visitors often mention the "Turkey Shed" for events and the resident cat that greets guests at the entrance.

